# Project Title

Node Version Manager Install Script - install script to manage node.js
versions in Linux and MacOS

## Getting Started

Install on linux based machine only.  Make sure bin/sh environment is enable

### Prerequisites

Update and install build-essentail

```
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install build-essential libssl-dev 
```

### Installing

Script Installation
```
./rvm.sh
```

Manual Installation 
1. Update dependencies and packages 

```
sudo apt-get update
```

2. Install curl 
```
sudo apt-get -y install apt-utils curl
```

3. Install mpapis public key 
```
gpg --keyserver hkp://keys.gnupg.net --recv-keys 409B6B1796C275462A1703113804BB82D39DC0E3
```

4. Install stable ruby version manager 
```
curl -sSL https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable --ruby
```

5. Add permission to rvm to current user 
```
usermod -aG rvm `id -un`
```

